=============================================
WHEN TO RESTART JEKYLL
=============================================

Jekyll automatically rebuilds your site when content or layouts change,
but some changes require a full restart of the Jekyll server.

---------------------------------------------
RESTART REQUIRED when you:
---------------------------------------------
1. Modify _config.yml
   - Any change to configuration (e.g., collections, plugins, permalinks)
   - Reason: Jekyll only reads config on startup.

2. Add or remove plugins (in _config.yml or Gemfile)
   - Reason: Plugins are loaded only once at boot.

3. Add or delete collections
   - e.g., adding a new folder like _comics or _episodes.
   - Reason: Collections are registered from _config.yml at startup.

4. Change directory structure
   - Moving folders, renaming directories, or changing where assets live.
   - Reason: Jekyll’s file watcher can lose track of paths.

5. Update site dependencies
   - e.g., after `bundle update` or installing new gems.

6. Switch branches (Git)
   - Reason: File watcher may not detect new layouts/includes on branch change.

7. Enable/disable incremental builds
   - If you toggle `--incremental` or modify related build flags.

---------------------------------------------
NO RESTART NEEDED when you:
---------------------------------------------
1. Edit Markdown files (.md)
   - Jekyll auto-rebuilds content pages.

2. Edit HTML layouts or includes
   - e.g., _layouts/, _includes/ — will hot-reload.

3. Edit CSS or JS (in assets/)
   - Changes picked up immediately unless bundled externally.

4. Add or change images
   - Adding new images in assets/ is detected and rebuilt automatically.

---------------------------------------------
TIPS
---------------------------------------------
- To restart quickly: press CTRL+C, then run `jekyll serve` again.
- If the site looks stale or partial updates stop showing, restart Jekyll.
- Incremental mode (`jekyll serve --incremental`) can occasionally miss changes —
  restart to force a full rebuild if something doesn’t update.

=============================================

